`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `tickTraps` scan pattern (armed → check enemies with break, else → tickCooldown) is the canonical game-loop shape for any "proximity sensor" mechanic. It's O(traps × enemies) per frame, which is fine at the expected scale (~10 traps, ~20 enemies).
- Config keys by `trapType` string (not array index) gives O(1) lookup and makes adding new trap types trivial — just add a JSON entry, no code changes needed.
